I used the 1/4 cup broth and it was enough--there's no need to have it swimming in sauce, although I didn't bother with cornstarch. Also cut the amount of soy sauce and didn't poach the tofu. And shuffled the order of cooking a bit to fit my idea of how much cooking each ingredient requires. I've made ma po many times with other recipes or more often just off the top of my head, and the tofu comes out fine without poaching. Toasting intensified the flavor of the (freshly ground) sichuan peppercorns (you can get them from Penzey's). I like hot, so added some sliced serranos--next time even more. Also added some peas and minced onion, considered but didn't add bell pepper. Maybe the extra veggies makes it less authentic, but this dish copes well with such changes.

