Rating: 0
just a quick clarification.... there are many references to the spice level or lack thereof in this dish and the blame has been leveled in many cases towards the presence of the sichuan peppercorn powder or lack thereof...... sichuan peppercorns aren't spicy.... if you want more spice, fry up some dried chili peppers at the beginning of the recipe in the oil or throw in some fresh green or red chilis as it's cooking..... sichuan peppercorns actually numb the tongue and add a really unique flavor to the dish.... this is an authentic recipe, but skip the poaching of the tofu and kick it up a notch-- the only caveat is that some spicy bean pastes are spicier than others, so be careful before you load it with chilis.....

