Rating: 3
I love MaPo Tofu and wanted to learn how to make the sauce, particularly because I find this dish varies wildly by each restaurant in which I order it. The first time I made this I followed the directions exactly, except I couldn't find a jar that was labeled "hot bean paste" so I substituted "black bean paste." It came out VERY tasty but not the right flavor. Then I searched the Lee Kum Kee brand website and discovered they make "Spicy Bean Sauce: Ma Po Sauce." It's part of their "one- step recipe sauces" collection. While the brand is common to my local grocery stores, this sauce is not. I had to shop at a local Asian market to find it. The meal was much closer to what you find in a restaurant though the purchased sauce is salty and has a slightly odd after taste. That time round I didn't add the extra flavors (broth, soy, garlic, ginger, powder) to it because it's meant to be the complete sauce in a jar. It made a quick and tasty dish - just cook the pork and add in tofu and green onion. I guess my third time round I'll have to try the sauce recommended with 2 TBSP of the Lee Kum Kee sauce. By the way, didn't poach the tofu either time and it came out fine.

